424.title: turbo.virtualization.libvirt.domains.<name>.title

425.body: The type specifies the hypervisor used for running the domain. The allowed values are driver specific, but include "xen", "kvm", "qemu" and "lxc". Type : one of "xen", "kvm", "qemu", "lxc" Default "kvm"
425.title: turbo.virtualization.libvirt.domains.<name>.type

428.body: The optional attribute cpuset is a comma-separated list of physical CPU numbers that domain process and virtual CPUs can be pinned to by default. Type : null or string Default null Example "1-4,^3,6"
428.title: turbo.virtualization.libvirt.domains.<name>.vcpu.cpuset

429.body: The optional attribute current can be used to specify whether fewer than the maximum number of virtual CPUs should be enabled. Since 0.8.5 Type : null or unsigned integer, meaning >=0 Default null
429.title: turbo.virtualization.libvirt.domains.<name>.vcpu.current

43.body: Extra configs to be appended Type : list of string Default []
43.title: turbo.networking.firewall.ip.mangle.appends

430.body: The optional attribute placement can be used to indicate the CPU placement mode for domain process. Type : null or one of "static", "auto" Default null
430.title: turbo.virtualization.libvirt.domains.<name>.vcpu.placement

431.body: The content of this element defines the maximum number of virtual CPUs allocated for the guest OS, which must be between 1 and the maximum supported by the hypervisor. Type : unsigned integer, meaning >=0 Default 1
431.title: turbo.virtualization.libvirt.domains.<name>.vcpu.size
